4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING BOARD OF HOUSING MEMBERSHIP; REQUIRING
5 AN ENROLLED TRIBAL MEMBER AND A VETERAN AS BOARD MEMBERS; AND AMENDING SECTION 2-
6 15-1814, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 2-15-1814, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "2-15-1814. Board of housing -- allocation -- composition -- quasi-judicial. (1) There is a board of
12 housing.
13 (2) The board consists of seven members appointed by the governor as provided in 2-15-124. The
14 members must be informed and experienced in housing, economics, or finance. At least one member must be
15 an enrolled member of a federally recognized tribe in Montana, and at least one member must be a veteran of
16 the United States armed forces.
17 (3) The board shall elect a presiding officer and other necessary officers.
18 (4) The board is designated as a quasi-judicial board for purposes of 2-15-124.
19 (5) The board is allocated to the department of commerce for administrative purposes only as
20 provided in 2-15-121.
21 (6) In compliance with the state pay plan, the department shall provide all staff and services to the
22 board that are determined by the board in conjunction with the department to be necessary for the purposes of
23 carrying out the board's programs. The department shall assess the board for reasonable costs.
24 (7) A member of the board may not be considered to have a conflict of interest under the
25 provisions of 2-2-201 merely because the member is a stockholder, officer, or employee of a lending institution
26 that may participate in the board's programs."
27 - END -
